<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910606-0105</DOCNO><DOCID>910606-0105.</DOCID><HL>   Acxiom Cuts Work Force by 7%</HL><DATE>06/06/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A5</SO><CO>   ACXM</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>INDUSTRIAL andamp; COMMERCIAL SERVICES, LEASING, CLEANING (ICS)INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL SERVICES (SVC)</IN><RE>ARKANSAS (AR)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   CONWAY, Ark. -- Acxiom Corp. said it terminated 7% of itswork force, or 111 employees, as part of an &quot;aggressive&quot;costcutting program &quot;in response to the current economicdownturn.&quot;   Acxiom said other measures include executive salarydecreases and a companywide bonus elimination for the currentyear.</LP><TEXT>   For the first quarter, Acxiom, a data processing companyfor the direct marketing industry, posted an earnings declineof almost 93% to $66,000, or one cent a share, from $960,000,or 20 cents a share in the year-earlier period. Sales roseabout 9% to $97.7 million from $89.7 million.</TEXT></DOC>